Diagnosis.
D. validior
is very close to
D. lesserti
but differs from it by a much larger terminal embolar apophysis, with a veil membranous part enlarged and denticulate for its entire length (
Fig. 47
), by its narrower atrium, more triangular (
Table 1
;
Fig. 45
), and the shape of the membranous coils, enlarged distally (
Fig. 46
).
